Northern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION>. Federal prosecutor <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Stearns </PERSON> said the case includes <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> telephone taps and evidence including radar and missile parts. <PERSON> Johnson </PERSON> is charged with developing for illegal export `` remote control detonation systems to facilitate a bombing campaign.'' <PERSON> Hoy </PERSON> is accused of working with <PERSON> Quigley </PERSON> to `` develop, test and export a missile and rocket system to be used against <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> helicopters in <LOCATION> Northern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION>.''
