ION> Hampshire </LOCATION> courts called for their return. <PERSON> Gray </PERSON> said Friday that <LOCATION> Montana </LOCATION> authorities must deliver the children to <LOCATION> Exeter </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> sheriff's officers at <LOCATION> Logan </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION>. They then will be taken to a foster home in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hampshire </LOCATION>, where all parental visits will be supervised. The children, who are in <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Denton </LOCATION>, will not be placed with either parent pending the <ORGANIZATION> Superior </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> hearing next month. <PERSON> Murabito </PERSON> did not return telephone calls from The <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION>, and his lawyer, <PERSON> Raymond </PERSON> <PERSON> Kellett </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Salem </LOCATION>, could not be reached for comment.
