ug traffickers following the slaying of one of their colleagues. Magistrate <PERSON> Carlos </PERSON> <PERSON> Valencia </PERSON> <PERSON> Garcia </PERSON> was fatally shot in <LOCATION> Bogota </LOCATION> on Wednesday, hours after rejecting appeals filed on behalf of two <LOCATION> Medellin </LOCATION> cartel leaders. `` It's terrifying what is happening in <LOCATION> Colombia </LOCATION>,'' Justice Minister <PERSON> Monica </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Grieff </PERSON> said on Friday. `` The only way to confront this challenge is by fighting together, the government, judges, the armed forces and the citizenry to stop the wave of violence,'' she said. In the past 10 years, 23 judges have been assassinated and officials blame nearly all of the slayings on drug dealers.
